Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:39.97,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}国安局
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.24,0:01:52.29,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尊敬的议长女士  恭喜您高升\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Madam Speaker, congratulations on your new position.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.29,0:01:53.49,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,让我先问您\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let me start by asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.49,0:01:55.51,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,您是否也像您议会的同事一样\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}do you, like your colleagues in the Senate,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.52,0:01:56.92,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,认为这些听证会\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}view these confirmation hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:01:58.97,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是走走形式呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as anything more than a formality?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.97,0:02:00.87,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,汤姆·柯特曼成为我们的总统\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tom Kirkman is our President
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.87,0:02:02.77,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是因为他不在国情咨文的现场\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because he wasn't - at the State of the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:05.80,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,彼得·麦克利什爆炸里活着  就成了英雄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Peter MacLeish is a hero because he lived through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.80,0:02:08.95,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而  要领导一个国家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Certainly, survival shouldn't be the only qualification
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.52,0:02:10.34,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}金布尔·霍斯拉滕议长讨论彼得·麦克利什
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:11.15,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,幸存不是唯一的资格  对吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when it comes to leading our country, should it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.69,0:02:13.36,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你威胁到她了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She's intimidated by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.52,0:02:17.35,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她已经在各大台说了一轮了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She's done everything from "Megyn Kelly" to "Jimmy Kimmel."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.55,0:02:21.31,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这可不只是"威胁"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Intimidated" isn't the word that comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.15,0:02:24.56,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,新议会中有162位独立人士\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}162 Independents in the new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.56,0:02:25.59,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她除了认可你为\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How can she read that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.59,0:02:28.03,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,美国第一位独立人士票选总统以外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as anything other than America's endorsement
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.03,0:02:30.30,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,别无他法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of their first Independent President?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:32.29,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相信我  她能找到方法的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Trust me. She'll find a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.61,0:02:37.12,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,议长女士  你希望我们能从\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Madam Speaker, - what do you hope to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.72,0:02:37.36,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}金布尔·霍斯拉滕议长讨论彼得·麦克利什
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.12,0:02:38.39,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,麦克利什议员的证词了解到什么呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from Congressman MacLeish's testimony?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.39,0:02:40.08,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她对我们的候选人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Has she done any irrevocable damage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:41.47,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成什么不可挽回的伤害了没\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to our nominee this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.84,0:02:43.98,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,没有  只是继续无休止地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, just continuing her never-ending quest
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.98,0:02:45.72,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,质疑他的提名资格\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to cast doubt on his qualifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.72,0:02:48.03,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她没有暗示参议院资格就算好的了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She'd be better off taking a cue from the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.03,0:02:49.09,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们清楚地表明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They made it perfectly clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:51.59,*Default,NTP,0,0,0,,谁也不想留下玩弄阴谋诡计的证据\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one wants to play politics with this confirmation.
